Error: All page content must be contained by landmarks
Error Description: Ensures all page content is contained by landmarks

Error: ARIA role must be appropriate for the element
Error Description: Ensures role attribute has an appropriate value for the element

Error: Heading levels should only increase by one
Error Description: Ensures the order of headings is semantically correct

Error: Page must have one main landmark
Error Description: Ensures the page has only one main landmark and each iframe in the page has at most one main landmark

Error: Elements must have sufficient color contrast
Error Description: Ensures the contrast between foreground and background colors meets WCAG 2 AA contrast ratio thresholds

Error: <html> element must have a lang attribute
Error Description: Ensures every HTML document has a lang attribute

Error: Page must contain a level-one heading
Error Description: Ensure that the page, or at least one of its frames contains a level-one heading

Error: Images must have alternate text
Error Description: Ensures elements have alternate text or a role of none or presentation

Error: Form elements must have labels
Error Description: Ensures every form element has a label

Error: The skip-link target should exist and be focusable
Error Description: Ensure all skip links have a focusable target

Error: Links must have discernible text
Error Description: Ensures links have discernible text

Error: <li> elements must be contained in a <ul> or <ol>
Error Description: Ensures <li> elements are used semantically

Error: Checkbox inputs with the same name attribute value must be part of a group
Error Description: Ensures related <input type="checkbox"> elements have a group and that the group designation is consistent

Error: Radio inputs with the same name attribute value must be part of a group
Error Description: Ensures related <input type="radio"> elements have a group and that the group designation is consistent

Error: <ul> and <ol> must only directly contain <li>, <script> or <template> elements
Error Description: Ensures that lists are structured correctly

Error: Documents must have <title> element to aid in navigation
Error Description: Ensures each HTML document contains a non-empty <title> element

Error: Form elements should have a visible label
Error Description: Ensures that every form element is not solely labeled using the title or aria-describedby attributes

Error: Text of buttons and links should not be repeated in the image alternative
Error Description: Ensure button and link text is not repeated as image alternative

Error: id attribute value must be unique
Error Description: Ensures every id attribute value is unique

Error: Headings must not be empty
Error Description: Ensures headings have discernible text

Error: All cells in a table element that use the headers attribute must only refer to other cells of that same table
Error Description: Ensure that each cell in a table using the headers refers to another cell in that table

Error: Frames must have title attribute
Error Description: Ensures <iframe> and <frame> elements contain a non-empty title attribute

Error: <dl> elements must only directly contain properly-ordered <dt> and <dd> groups, <script> or <template> elements
Error Description: Ensures <dl> elements are structured correctly

Error: IDs of active elements must be unique
Error Description: Ensures every id attribute value of active elements is unique

Error: lang attribute must have a valid value
Error Description: Ensures lang attributes have valid values

Error: ARIA roles used must conform to valid values
Error Description: Ensures all elements with a role attribute use a valid value

Error: scope attribute should be used correctly
Error Description: Ensures the scope attribute is used correctly on tables

Error: ARIA attributes must conform to valid values
Error Description: Ensures all ARIA attributes have valid values

Error: IDs used in ARIA and labels must be unique
Error Description: Ensures every id attribute value used in ARIA and in labels is unique
